Joseph Shabalala died this morning after a long illness. Ladysmith Black Mambazo group manager, Xolani Majozi reflects on Shabalala's life. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Ladysmith Black Mambazo founder Joseph Shabalala has died. The 78-year-old lead singer of the global iconic Ladysmith Black Mambazo died on Tuesday morning after a long illness. READ: Richard Maponya dies aged 99 After five decades as an active musician, Shabalala announced his retirement in 2013. Ladysmith Black Mamba has toured the world sharing the stage with global hitmakers. The group has won five Grammy Awards.